track.name: Louie Louie
comments: Of all the versions of Louie Louie (and there are a lot), this is pretty much the best
Wow, best version I've ever heard!
Can´t stop dancing :D classic Skinhead tune!!!!

@d0l : i did not mean to come across as an "elitest" i wouldnt even want to be associated as one, I mean that if it wasnt for such films as " This Is England " etc, music like this would not be anywhere as near as popular as it is. I got my first taste of ska/reggae at a Hells Angels rally in Surrey UK and since have built up a rather eclectic music taste.

This would be a great tune for a scene in a movie about Skinheads, I don't know, something like a slow-motion walking montage about the day in the life of a skin...what?! It's already been done? Well there you have it!
groovy Louie, impressed by these great musicians

skengmanben, did you never consider the possibility that they would not have heard these great songs otherwise? it doesn't matter where it's heard, as long as it's heard. that elitist attitude towards where you hear music is pretty annoying.
@Alliban yeah that is really true it amazes me how people only give it a chance once theyve heard it on tv.
rise of the skins! thats SKA!
